    "content" : "Thanks for the comments chaps, I really wasn't sure about cutting off the chassis legs, but its done now, I want to keep the bus and keep it in the garage and this is the only way \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" alt=\":roll:\" title=\"Roll Eyes\"> I found the receipt when I'd bought them it was dated 2003, either the 1st or second CE irs chassis legs made for a bd, hence they needed a small amount of moding.The creative kit is well built. One spring plate has been an absolute so-in-so to get off, we ended up cutting off 5-10mm at a time from where it joined the torsion bar and eventually came off, (see: 4 years!!!) so now I just need to measure the degrees and fit the '68 spring plates (thanks shawn for the advice), hmmm 3\" or 6\" drop \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" alt=\":wink:\" title=\"Wink\"> Then I will fit the adjusters to the front beam. Hopefully Dad will get some more welding done to the bus before he sells up and it comes down here, cos then it's up to me to finish the metal work \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_eek.gif\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" alt=\"8O\" title=\"eek\"> \n<br> \n<br> hey nick one for you the strip lamp in the roof above the bulkhead, oh yeah \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" alt=\":wink:\" title=\"Wink\"> \n<br> \n<br> \n<img src=\"http://images.thesamba.com/vw/gallery/pix/410368.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\">",
